ogical aspects of masculinity, The Masculine Self in Late Medieval England offers a uniquely comprehensive account of the exterior and interior lives of medieval men.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  amasculinity, gender, men, manhood, self, identity, medieval, england, patriarchy, power, aggression, martial, heroism, knights, chivalry, black death, protestant reformation, honesty, self-restraint, control, domination, hierarchy, livelihood, reputation, conflict, husbandry, adultery, sexuality, clergy, fatherhood, nonfiction, history, desire, romance, ywain and gawain, narcissism, green knight, perceval of galles, merlin, king arthur, literature, lybeaus desconus, bevis hampton.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022656955040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226569598423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226569598/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles